<TITLE> 16 workers fired at Savar textile mill </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Savar, Jan 8 (bdnews24.com)--The authorities of Panna Textile Limited, owned by former Awami League MP Mokbul Hossain, fired 16 workers for their support of protests against the mill's management. With the outbreak of the news, security forces were dispatched to the location to prevent any unwanted consequences. Assistant general manager of the mill Khalid Ahmed said: "Twenty-two workers were fired for inciting the protest." "Out of these 6 women workers later understood their mistake and apologised so they remain in our employment." He also said that the fired workers have been paid 3 months salary and an attendance bonus as per labour laws. Savar Police Station officer in charge Abul Khayer Fakir said: "Police will be deployed all round the clock so that the fired workers cannot create any disturbances." bdnews24.com/
